OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FThe west staying mostly cloudy,
OL,6,Fperhaps some patchy drizzle for the
OL,7,FIsles with some mist and fog there
OL,8,Flater, while the east remains dry and
OL,9,Fvery warm with bright or sunny spells.
OL,10,FMainly light winds.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FCloudy in west with coastal
OL,13,Ffog. Some rain developing across the
OL,14,FIsles, this extending to the Northwest
OL,15,Fmainland during the night.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FSome bright spells at first in
OL,18,Fthe south and east. Cloud and rain to
OL,19,Fthe northwest of the Great Glen,
OL,20,Fextending to Moray Firth in afternoon,
OL,21,Flocally heavy, south drier.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
